                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="208718" author="pjones" created="Tue, 19 Sep 2017 02:48:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;ok thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="208714" author="sebg-crd-pm" created="Tue, 19 Sep 2017 02:02:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There is no question now. Thanks. (set admin_nodemap=1, chown by root)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="208111" author="emoly.liu" created="Tue, 12 Sep 2017 08:04:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=sebg-crd-pm&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;sebg-crd-pm&quot;&gt;sebg-crd-pm&lt;/a&gt;, do you still have question about this ticket?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="199565" author="sebg-crd-pm" created="Mon, 19 Jun 2017 01:54:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have set admin_nodemap=1, trusted_nodemap=0  then it works fine.&lt;br/&gt;
Just one nodemap can not chown if set admin_nodemap=1, trusted_nodemap=1.&lt;br/&gt;
I will test it again then report more detail information of environment.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="199469" author="pjones" created="Fri, 16 Jun 2017 16:11:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Assigning to Emoly for any follow on quesitons&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="199427" author="adilger" created="Fri, 16 Jun 2017 04:48:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This should work if both the source and destination UID are in the nodemap, and root operations are allowed on the nodemap. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
